The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and clustering processes, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and data mining (cs.DM). The focus on K-Means algorithm and feature weighting further supports these sub-categories.
